title: Eatontown Circle
text: The Eatontown Circle was a <a href="traffic%20circle">traffic circle</a> in <a href="Eatontown%2C%20New%20Jersey">Eatontown</a>, <a href="New%20Jersey">New Jersey</a>, located at the intersection of <a href="Route%2035%20%28New%20Jersey%29">Route 35</a>, <a href="Route%2036%20%28New%20Jersey%29">Route 36</a>, Wall Street and near Wyckoff Road (<a href="County%20Route%20547%20%28New%20Jersey%29">CR 547</a>), near the <a href="Monmouth%20Mall">Monmouth Mall</a>. At the time of its construction, the southwest quadrant was built on a farm owned by the Valentino Family from nearby <a href="Long%20Branch%2C%20New%20Jersey">Long Branch</a>.
